\end_inset

 1 h 20 minutes after the ink was introduced more clearly shows the lagging
 behind of the ink in the unsaturated zone, where there is vertually no
 flow.
 The sharp contrast of the water velocity at the boundary of the unsaturated
 and the saturated zone is also indicative of the coarse material used in
 the model, there is hardly a transition zone.
 The figure allows to estimate the horizontal flow velocity in the unsaturated
 zone to be about 1/4th to 1/5th of that of the top of the saturated zone.
\end_layout

