\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

.
 The inflow at the canal of the streamline approaching along the op of the
 saturated zone, which is above the canal level at 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

, clearly demonstrates the development of a seepage zone.
 A seepage face is special boundary outflow condition along which head and
 elevation are the same.
 A seepage zone needs some attention when modeling it.
\end_layout

